      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) with documented V&V history; solver release notes and regression test suite reviewed.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 is a commercially validated solver with ISO 9001-certified development process. Internal regression suite covers relevant turbulence and transport models. Gradation 2 achieved: solver documentation and release-level QA records reviewed and on file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests performed on canonical rotating-flow benchmark; observed order within 10% of theoretical.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to a simplified rotating annulus problem. Observed spatial order of accuracy 1.87 vs theoretical 2.0 for the k-omega SST discretisation — within 10% tolerance. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation GCI < 5% on primary QoI (volume-averaged shear stress) across three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (3.2 M, 9.6 M, 28.8 M cells) used. GCI on volume-averaged shear stress: 3.1% (fine-medium), 3.8% (medium-coarse). Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement; Gradation 3 awarded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions (2.5 L/min and 3500 RPM nominal) reproduced within ±2% for flow rate and ±10 RPM for speed. Fluid temperature controlled at 37°C ±0.5°C. Boundary condition mapping documented in test plan TP-CBP-001. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index (NIH) compared against published FDA experimental data; agreement within ±25% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values at 5 operating points compared against Herbertson et al. (2015) FDA benchmark data. Maximum deviation 18.4%, mean deviation 11.2%. All 5 points within ±25% acceptance band. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion and is computed from model outputs without intermediate surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "RH index is computed directly from CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time fields using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. This QoI is the regulatory acceptance criterion for 510(k) hemolysis comparison. No surrogate substitution required. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties match COU device class and operating envelope to within documented similarity criteria.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry used in the COU. Reynolds number range and fluid (bovine blood analog) match COU conditions. Geometric similarity index 0.97. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence monitored; residuals below 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations run to continuity residual < 1e-6, momentum residuals < 1e-6, turbulence quantities < 1e-5. Global mass imbalance < 0.005%. Convergence plots archived in simulation log SL-CBP-2024-03. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition inputs and post-processing scripts version-controlled and peer-reviewed.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup conducted by senior analyst (not the original modeller). Boundary condition input files and post-processing scripts stored in Git repository with commit-level traceability. Two discrepancies found and corrected during review. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by literature review and sensitivity study; hemolysis sub-model validated against published power-law correlation data.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected based on published rotating machinery benchmark studies (Fraser et al. 2011). Sensitivity study comparing SST vs realizable k-epsilon shows <8% difference in NIH. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model validated against Heuser & Opitz (1980) data. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in blood viscosity, hematocrit, and inlet velocity profile characterised and propagated through model to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Input uncertainty quantification for patient-specific blood rheology parameters (viscosity, hematocrit variability) and inlet velocity profile was identified as beyond the scope of the current submission timeline. A nominal Newtonian viscosity of 0.0035 Pa·s was applied without formal uncertainty propagation. This factor is carried as not-assessed pending a planned sensitivity study in the next submission cycle. The assessment team considers this acceptable given available validation data, though no quantitative basis for this judgement has been established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Statistical characterisation of experimental sample variability (device-to-device, lot-to-lot) documented and accounted for in validation comparison.",
      "rationale": "Characterisation of device-to-device manufacturing variability in the FDA benchmark test samples was not available from the published dataset. The original Herbertson et al. data reports mean values without full sample-level statistics. A formal statistical treatment of test sample variability is outside the current scope and deferred. The team notes this limitation but has not quantified its impact on the validation conclusions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Equivalency between validation experiment input parameters and COU simulation input parameters demonstrated for all primary boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Mapping table prepared comparing validation experiment boundary conditions (flow rate, RPM, fluid properties, temperature) against COU simulation inputs. All primary parameters within equivalency tolerance. Minor deviations in inlet turbulence intensity (5% vs 3% in validation) assessed as negligible via sensitivity run showing <2% change in NIH. Gradation 2 achieved."
    }
  ],
